theorem Topology.frontier_subset_closure_inter_closure_compl {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    frontier (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) ∩ closure (Aᶜ : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  -- `hx` gives the two defining properties of `frontier A`
  have hx_clA : x ∈ closure (A : Set X) := hx.1
  have hx_not_intA : x ∉ interior (A : Set X) := hx.2
  -- We now show `x ∈ closure (Aᶜ)`
  have hx_clAcompl : x ∈ closure (Aᶜ : Set X) := by
    classical
    by_contra hxc
    -- Consider the open neighbourhood `U = (closure (Aᶜ))ᶜ` of `x`
    have hU_open : IsOpen ((closure (Aᶜ : Set X))ᶜ) :=
      (isClosed_closure (s := (Aᶜ : Set X))).isOpen_compl
    have hxU : x ∈ (closure (Aᶜ : Set X))ᶜ := by
      simp [hxc]
    -- `U` is actually contained in `A`
    have hU_sub_A : (closure (Aᶜ : Set X))ᶜ ⊆ (A : Set X) := by
      intro y hy
      by_contra hy_notA
      have hy_in_Acompl : y ∈ (Aᶜ : Set X) := by
        simpa [Set.mem_compl] using hy_notA
      have : y ∈ closure (Aᶜ : Set X) := subset_closure hy_in_Acompl
      exact (Set.mem_compl at hy; exact hy this).elim
    -- Hence `x ∈ interior A`, contradicting `hx_not_intA`
    have : x ∈ interior (A : Set X) := by
      have hU_in_intA : (closure (Aᶜ : Set X))ᶜ ⊆ interior (A : Set X) :=
        interior_maximal hU_sub_A hU_open
      exact hU_in_intA hxU
    exact hx_not_intA this
  exact And.intro hx_clA hx_clAcompl

theorem Topology.frontier_closure_of_dense {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense A → frontier (closure (A : Set X)) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  intro hDense
  simpa [hDense.closure_eq, frontier_univ]
